<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>AC Milan have completed the signing of highly-rated Italy midfielder Sandro Tonali from Brescia on loan with an option to make the move permanent.</p>

<p>Tonali, 20, has made 89 appearances for Brescia, who were relegated in July, and scored seven goals.</p>

<p>The 20-year-old has joined for an initial loan fee of £9million, with the option to buy him outright for £14m next summer in a deal that could rise to £32m, according to Goal.</p>

<p>AC Milan have completed the signing of highly-rated midfielder Sandro Tonali from Brescia</p>

<p>The 20-year-old (middle-right) was one of Serie A's most sought-after players this summer</p>

<p>He made his senior Italy debut last October and has three international caps.</p>

<p>'He is one of the most promising young talents in international football. Sandro has a love for the club and an understanding of its values that will add to what we want to build together,' Milan CEO Ivan Gazidis said in a statement.</p>

<p>Tonali attracted interest from Barcelona and Manchester United after consistently impressing for struggling Brescia.</p>

<p>Huge things are expected of Tonali in his homeland, with the player repeatedly compared against the iconic Andrea Pirlo.</p>

<p>Huge things are expected of Tonali, with the playmaker often compered to Andrea Pirlo</p>

<p>Tonali previously looked set for a move to Milan's bitter rivals Inter, but turned them down once he was made aware of the Rossoneri's interest. </p>

<p>'We are excited to welcome Sandro to the Rossoneri family,' said club legend and current technical director Paolo Maldini.</p>

<p>'As a talented, young midfielder he will not only embrace the values of AC Milan but also make a significant contribution to the future success of the club.'</p>
